lass=m><span class=title>   Re: Beastmaster Class</span><hr size=1> I'll respond to a few of those points...<br>
<br>
1)  Mages stop getting equal level pets when casting at lvl 24.  Beastlords stop getting equal level pets at 39.  That makes me assume that innately, beastlord pets will be of a higher level.  Higher level = better endgame pets.  Damage output of an equal level mage and necro pet are much less, mage pets at 39 hit for... 34 ?  BL starts quadding and hits for 39 and the max mage DD proc on a pet is 35?  BL is upwards of 60.  Yes, I agree that lvl 47, 48... Beastlords are going suck some major ass... they'll be a lvl 48 with a lvl 37-38 pet.<br>
<br>
2)  End game armour will allow Beastlords to have higher AC than druids easily.  BL's can wear Phase spider Carapace, which right there shows that Verant will be allowing them to eventually have the high AC items.  I even think that Beastlords can wear ToV Dragon Skin armour... that's some pretty high AC there.  Hp's on the pet are much higher than the mage and necro pets - dueled a lvl 49 necro pet ( they give you... what lvl 40 pet ? ) with the 39 pet - and although he was highly outdamaged, he lost by a sliver of health.<br>
<br>
3)  No clue about the AC on the pets... but with pretty twinked gear on me, I dont notice that much of a difference between what I'm getting hit for and what the pet does when I stand back and chain heal.<br>
<br>
4)  The low level slow sucks.. yes - until you get the only other one at lvl 51.  Though Togors is much more than a 30%.  I think when BL's first get the spell its 40%, and goes up 1% each level.  SO - lvl 60 BL will have a 51% slow... not bad at all.  Self healing power is really really bad - yes.  Pet healing power is mana wise about 30% more efficient than personal cleric heals.  In a 6 person group, BL's will be a VERY welcome addition.  In the end-game... I see this.   Beastlords h2h cap at 225... monk caps at 255.  I dont see 'that' much difference between the 2 other than double attack which BL's dont get.  I'm also assuming that the pet can more than adequately make up for the lack of double attack.  <br>
<br>
     Beastlords WITh the pet will be a high damage output melee class... I mean.. they can use the same weapons as the monk... 16/18 weapons ??? Can't say they're not going to be a good damage dealer.<br>
<br>
5)  Yes - pet penalty sucks ass... but I'm thinking in the long run it will be worth it.<br>
<br>
6)  Because of the higher level pets, and higher HP - I'm hoping ( as it has yet to be seen ) that they can withstand Dragon Fear and AE enough so that they can hold out in a high end encounter.  Guess we'll all see !<br>
<br>
All in all, I'm enjoying the BL immensely - I see not that many drawbacks yet... have yet to bring him into the end-game mobs ( lvl 43 still )  so I CAN say without a doubt so far... that if you are one who doesnt have THAT much EQ time on your hands, and you want a class that can solo and give you the most enjoyment and non-dependancy for your buck - Beastlords will do you fine.  If you are not involved with 100% raids and engame mobs... you might enjoy iy also even when at lvl 60.<br>
<br>
Hope this all helps<br>
<br>
MUFAT!<br>
soon to be known as<br>
<br>
VRASHN! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umufat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mufat</A> at: 12/14/01 7:53:14 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unechigladerunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nechi Gladerunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 217<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/14/01 12:23:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Beastmaster Class</span><hr size=1> Ok in responce<br>
<br>
1) While mages start getting pets that are not of the same level, they have nukes to fall back on.  Those progress with them.  Plus their pets even being of lower level are highly specialized.  Each has its place in a situation.  BTW I am not sure about the lower level pets but the 50 through 54 pets have a 60-141damage proc.  Earth Pet is about 60, Air is 60, Water is 141 and Fire doesn't have a proc but rather spells that do up to 220damage.<br>
<br>
2) Yes the very high end stuff will give them good ac or REALLY expensive twink gear but for the mainstream no... they can't even wear things like Crystal Chitin Armor which a druid can.  Shaman have higher ac then they do too and they are the parent class of them.  BTW Necro Pets don't have that much HP.  Have it duel a Mage Earth Pet or Fire Pet.<br>
<br>
3) The problem when sitting back and chain healing is the class has the hybrid penilty for casting.  They have a 185 max meditation till level 50 and even then don't get as high as other casters.  They also don't get specialization.<br>
<br>
4) They don't get torgors.  They only get a 30% slow at 50 and a 50% at 60.  They &quot;were&quot; going to get it and it then it would be a different story. A cap of 225 is a HUGE difference.  It is the difference between hitting and missing and you will start to see a lot of Miss Miss Miss Miss.  A Shadow Knight or a Paladin are going to be doing more damage than a Beastlord without a pet.  It also leaves them without any support spells really either that are going to make a difference.<br>
<br>
5) ...<br>
<br>
6) We will have to see with that but I think we while find the same to be true.<br>
